mous and excellent person, or rather one chosen of God likewise unto eternal life and salvation; and whose children also were walking in the truth, and here send their Christian salutation to their aunt; very likely those sister's children lived at Ephesus, where John resided.","content_hash":"a1eead4ca023428a01b1e6d5221e46b4d74936cb","links":[],"source_href":"../../gill/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","text_hash":"a1eead4ca023428a01b1e6d5221e46b4d74936cb"}],"2":[{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"2_john","chapter":1,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":1,"verse":1},"text_hash":"e63d52746573ca21a276692f10aaab5a13f6f420"},{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../gill/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","source_ref":{"book_id":"2_john","chapter":1,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":1,"verse":2}}],"3":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../pulpit/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"pulpit","source_name":"Pulpit Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"2_john","chapter":1,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":1,"verse":3}},{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"2_john","chapter":1,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":1,"verse":1},"text_hash":"e63d52746573ca21a276692f10aaab5a13f6f420"},{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../gill/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","source_ref":{"book_id":"2_john","chapter":1,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":1,"verse":3}}],"4":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../ellicott/2_john/1.htm","source_id":"ellicott","source_name":"Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers","source_ref":{"book_id":"2_john","chapter":1,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":1,"verse":4}},{"match":"direct","source_href":"..